Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of an OpenCV-Python code using Haar Cascade algorithm for object and face detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of UAVs for border security and surveillance, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms such as Voila-jones algorithm for human detection and tracking suggests that the paper could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the reduced processing time, which could indicate that it falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of video and image databases for testing the Python code suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
